						<summary>

						<p>Stone in the backyard <hi rend="italic">(doḍḍi)</hi> of the house of Juvvimānu-Pōchi-reḍḍi.</p>						

						<p>Circa 8th century.</p>						

						<p>This damaged record refers to an attack on Nandakuru and mentions Bhūpaditya who is said to have been governing Rēnāḍu. The name of the king is lost. It records a gift of land.</p>						

						</summary>
